cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.DS 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) - The paper deals with image processing and classification, which falls under the domain of computer vision. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper discusses the impact of MNIST experiments on reported testing performances, which is related to machine learning. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper deals with the reconstruction of a dataset and its impact on classification accuracy, which is related to artificial intelligence. 
4. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) - The paper involves tracing each MNIST digit to its NIST source and its metadata, which is related to information retrieval. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper involves reconstructing the complete MNIST test set with 60,000 samples, which is related to data structures and algorithms.
